title: For Sale/Trade:  Ascend Armory UltraLight Rifle w/ optic
postcontent: I can accept debit/credit cards for a small fee and I am not a dealer. Trades okay as well. I have put exactly 35 rounds through this gun.  Here are the full details on what makes up this gun.The billet receiver set is from Ascend Armory and is by far the nicest one on the market.  Everything on it is or can be fully ambidexterous, with the exception of the direction the casings eject.  The short throw selector is also from Ascend.  The majority of the LPK came preinstalled from Ascend.  The trigger is a Chip McCormick 3.5lb flat.  The buffer tube and end plate are from Battle Arms Development and the model is the Sabertube.  The grip is also aluminum and from Taran Tactical.  I wrapped it with paracord to soften it and also beef it up a bit.  It feels great either way.  The buffer is the JP Captured Silent Buffer and is hands down the best on the market.    The barrel is from Faxon and is 14.5".  To make this a legal rifle, the Precision Armament M4-72 was pinned and welded in place by Shane at SR Tactical in Nixa.  The adjustable gas block is a low profile model from Superlative Arms and also has a bleed off feature.  It also has its own spring loaded tensioning pin with positive clicks on each turn.  The carbon fiber handguard weighs in at only 5oz with the barrel nut and is from Brigand Arms.  It is the Edge model. Its extremely strong and extremely lightweight.  The port door is from V Seven and is the minimalist design.  Its also titanium to save weight.  The skeletonized Nickel Boron lightweight BCG is from AIM.  The charging handle and extended latch is from Strike.Overall length of the gun is 32.125" and weighs 4lbs 13.3oz.  The barrel is a 5.56 and can safely shoot .223 Remington as well.All items on this weapon were purchased new specifically for this build.Also included but not pictured is a picatinny rail riser and a Burris FastFire 3 reflex sight. Also purchased new for this job. For more pics, please inquire and I will send a link to view the other photos.Total price of this build, as pictured, was right at $2250.
